          description:
            "<p>Demonstration of Advanced Caution and Warning System Software with the Orion EFT-1 flight and subsequent ongoing evaluation for fault management of Orion.<br /> <br /> ASO developed Advanced Caution and Warning (ACAWS) software to assist flight controllers and astronauts in identifying and responding to faults.  This technology was first demonstrated during the Exploration Flight Test 1 (EFT-1) mission; the software provided flight controllers with insight into EFT-1 performance throughout the 6+ hour mission.  Subsequently, the software has been matured to provide the same insight for astronauts, and has been scaled to run on embedded processors such as those onboard spacecraft.  It has been employed in joint simulations with flight controllers and astronauts in preparation for Exploration Mission 1 (EM-1).<br /> <br /> This work is described in the following publications:</p>  <p>Gordon B. Aaseng and Eric Barszcz and Henry Valdez and Haifa Moses. Scaling Up Model-Based Diagnostic and Fault Effects Reasoning for Spacecraft.  Proceedings of the AIAA Conference on Spac Operations, September 2016.</p>  <p>G. Aaseng, J. Frank. Transitioning Autonomous Systems Technology Research to a Flight Software Environment.  Proceedings of the AIAA Conference on Spac Operations, September 2016.<br /> <br /> Gordon B. Aaseng, Adam Sweet, and John Ossenfort. Performance Analysis of an Autonomous Fault Management System.  Proceedings of the 2018 AIAA SPACE and Astronautics Forum and Exposition, 2018 </p> ",
